description:
Get any yeast nutrient you can think of at my shop!  http://www.biyhomebrewsupply.com/collections/chemicals/nutrients

Yeast nutrient is a chemical added to your wort or must that helps the yeast propagate faster, helps your brew get fermenting quicker, and overall helps the yeast attenuate your batch much better.  This basically means that the use of a yeast nutrient will help get the the yeast going quicker and will help ensure your brew is more completely fermented by the end.  The most basic yeast nutrient is diammonium phosphate (or oftentimes a blend of urea and ammonium phosphate).  There are also much more complex and advanced yeast nutrients, such as those manufactured by Wyeast, that also contain vitamins, minerals, amino acids, and other proprietary blends of chemicals and compounds that all contribute to a quicker, more thorough fermentation.
title: Basics of Home Brewing:  What is yeast nutrient?

----

THE PATH OF WILDNESS

The Path of Wildness is easy to find
The course of a stream
Leaves blown in the wind
A beast's track through the brush
And the direction of our first inclination

The Path of Wildness is an answer and response to a prescribed way of life which may leave some individuals with a sense that their living is little more than a series of pre-determined, step-like episodes between birth and death. The stages of living between these events: childhood, adolescence, adulthood, parenthood and senior are themselves natural and in accord with the needs of the species and most individuals. Many find their satisfaction in living this course and to these individuals I have little or nothing to say. Others though long for something more; something innate, genetic and seemingly calling. Adventure and change can give a degree of satisfaction and relief yet even these may seem too tame. To those who feel drawn to something beyond the entertainment and stimulation of senses I offer a walk along The Path of Wildness. Don't bother penciling the event in your schedule, preparing a pack with goodies and supplies or even inviting a friend along, for this experience is along the course of your first inclination and you must surely always go alone.

Learn more about The Path of Wildness here:
http://wp.me/P5A2F-As

description:
With a success rate of over 85%, the Reed Procedure ® peripheral neurostimulator headache treatment has already provided headache relief to, and restored the lives of, hundreds of patients suffering from debilitating chronic migraine headaches. Dr. Reed, and the partner physicians at Reed Migraine Centers, are the most experienced specialists in the world at occipital nerve stimulator therapies, as well as all other implantable peripheral nerve stimulation techniques for headache treatment. Indeed, in 2009 Dr. Reed's original medical research paper on the technique of "Combined Supraorbital and Occipital Nerve Stimulation" was honored with the International Headache Society's "Cephalalgia Award." This prestigious citation is awarded in recognition of the best original medical research paper published by the journal "Cephalalgia" over the previous year. Indeed, continuing our commitment to ongoing research, in 2012 Reed Migraine Centers teamed with the Mayo Clinic, Duke University, and other top centers, and published the results of St. Jude's foundational multicenter study on "Occipital Neurostimulation for Chronic Migraine". Reed Migraine Centers has offices and partner physicians currently in Dallas, New York, Chicago, Miami and other metropolitan areas.

For those patients suffering from debilitating headaches and seeking migraine relief, Reed Migraine Centers invites you to view our other patient information videos on peripheral neurostimulation that we have made available at the Reed Migraine YouTube Channel at http://www.youtube.com/user/ReedMigraine. More detailed information, including our schedule of patient information seminars, is also available at our website, http://www.reedmigraine.com
title: Dr. Ken Reed Explains Nature of a Peripheral Nerve Stimulator for Migraine Treatment

The Atlantic Coast Conference (ACC) is a collegiate athletic conference in the United States in which its fifteen member universities compete in the National Collegiate Athletic Association (NCAA's) Division I, with its football teams competing in the Football Bowl Subdivision (FBS), the highest levels for athletic competition in US-based collegiate sports. The ACC sponsors competition in twenty-five sports with many of its member institutions' athletic programs held in high regard nationally. ACC teams and athletes have claimed dozens of national championships in multiple sports throughout the conference's history. Generally, the ACC's top athletes and teams in any particular sport in a given year are considered to be among the top collegiate competitors in the nation. The ACC is considered to be one of the six collegiate power conferences, all of which enjoy extensive media coverage and automatic qualifying for their football champion into the Bowl Championship Series (BCS). With the advent of the College Football Playoff in 2014, the ACC will be one of five conferences with a contractual tie-in to an "access bowl", the successors to the BCS.

Founded in 1953 in Greensboro, North Carolina, by seven universities located in the South Atlantic States, the conference added additional members in late 1953, 1979, 1991, 2004, and 2013. The 2004 and 2013 additions extended the conference's footprint into the Northeast and Midwest. The most recent expansion in 2013 saw the additions of the University of Notre Dame, the University of Pittsburgh, and Syracuse University. In 2012, the University of Maryland's Board of Regents voted to withdraw from the ACC to join the Big Ten Conference. On November 28, 2012, the ACC's Council of Presidents voted unanimously to invite the University of Louisville as a full member, replacing Maryland.

READ THIS BEFORE POSTING!

Video Made by: Anti Noob, I am not Anti Noob, I am AfRo SaUcE.

This description is not meant to show how to "make the ghost come" cause there is really no such thing as a ghost so please stop sending messages asking how to make him come.

The only reason im posting this video is to explain that the Ghost Of Lockout is not a mod and is in fact a network glitch..

Before you all come up in here spamming that this is a mod, its not and I'll explain. Here's how it works: The "Ghost" is actually a person in the game that the host (in this case, Anti Noob) can only see as a default spartan sliding around with no walking animation. Now you're probably saying "How can he have no walking animation without a mod?" Well, you cant mod spartans and elites to have no animation or you're game is bound to freeze. That also goes for the "auto-sticking". On Anti Noobs screen he sees the "ghost" of course as I said before a default white spartan and he is sliding everywhere and has no animations.. this also means he really doesnt have a turning animation. How he has the grenade throwing and shooting animations is caused by the lag giving him those attributes. Now on the person that is the "ghost" 's screen he is actually walking and turning around and doing all sorts of stuff that you cant see on Anti Noobs screen. Another way to prove its not a mod is that back when this video was made it was IMPOSSIBLE to mod old maps (I.E. Lockout) on Xbox Live. As you can see this is filmed on Xbox Live because you can see Lag/Ping bars next to their names whenever he holds back or dies. All you guys that think its a Bungie/Xbox Live Admin... think again, that is the stupidest thing you could ever think of that would happen in Halo 2 more or less Xbox Live. Admins cannot join your games without names nor can they spy on you or any crap like that. No such thing or bungie would have revealed it by now. There is no frame skipping, I dont see why someone would frame skip to lie about something on a damn video game. No frame skipping! This video isn't new by the way its well over a year old, before you could mod old maps online... Anyway yeah I think thats about it. No mod just a network glitch.

Note: I cant reply in the comments thingy cause for some reason it keeps saying I need flash player or its turned off but when I go to a different vid it works.. So If you want me to reply to you I'll just PM you or somethin.

Edit: Stop messaging me saying "I believe you, my friend said he saw a ghost in Halo 1" or "my friend saw one in system link when he was waiting for his friends to join at a LAN party." That's bullshit, it only happens on Live.

description:
Buffalo

is with 261 310 inhabitants, the second largest city of the U.S. state of New York. In the metropolitan area of ​​Buffalo - Niagara over 1.2 million inhabitants. Buffalo is the administrative seat of Erie County and is located not far from Niagara Falls, on the northeast corner of Lake Erie . Today Buffalo is a modern industrial city and port .

The name comes from Buffalo " Buffalo Creek ", which from 1759 to 1760 first appeared on a map ; the origin of this name is not assignable .

In German-speaking countries Buffalo probably best known for the poem John Maynard by Theodor Fontane. A hint of this poem bronze plaque was unveiled in Buffalo in 1997.

The Art Deco - style built City Hall Buffalo's 115 meters one of the tallest public building in the United States. It is on the National Register of Historic Places , as well as about seventy additional objects in the city. The proposed by Frank Lloyd Wright Darwin D. Martin House is a National Historic Landmark.

LION

After the tiger , the lion is the second largest cat making it the largest land predator in Africa. A male lion has a body length of 170 to 250 centimeters , a shoulder height of up to 123 centimeters and a tail length of approximately one meter. Adult males arrive on an average body weight of 190 kilograms. The variation ranges 150-225 kg in exceptional cases up to 272 kg. Females are at 140 and 175 cm body length , a shoulder height of 100 centimeters and a 85 cm long tail considerably more delicate and have a body weight of around 126 kilograms. On average, lions have a greater shoulder height than Tiger , but are overall slightly shorter. The largest lions now live in southern Africa , the smallest in Asia. In zoos and circuses held males reach due to good feeding occasionally a weight of over 300 kilograms.

The often cited maximum head fuselage length of 250 cm , however, are not attested sure of today's lions and fit at best to the greatest forms of Pleistocene lions , such as the American lion . After Mazák , the average total length , ie the length including the tail, with today's male lions about 260 to 270 cm , rarely more than 285 cm. The most credible traditional measures of length for lion lying at about 305-310 cm total length, measured in a direct line ( between pegs ) from the nose to the tip of the tail to the north in an animal from the area of Lake Victoria .

description:
Animation of occlusal cycle in Wurmiella excavata P1 elements, using synchrotron radiation X-ray computed micro-tomography models of P1 element pair ROM 61381. Dextral element in yellow, sinistral element in blue. See main text for details. 

- Jawless vertebrate had world's sharpest teeth
Conodonts used minuscule tooth points to apply large pressure to food.
Nature 14 March 2012 DOI: doi:10.1038/nature.2012.10211
http://www.nature.com/news/jawless-vertebrate-had-world-s-sharpest-teeth-1.10211

Reference
The sharpest tools in the box? Quantitative analysis of conodont element functional morphology
Proc. R. Soc. B March 14, 2012, doi: 10.1098/rspb.2012.0147 
http://rspb.royalsocietypublishing.org/content/early/2012/03/09/rspb.2012.0147
PDF: http://rspb.royalsocietypublishing.org/content/early/2012/03/09/rspb.2012.0147.full.pdf

Abstract
Conodonts have been considered the earliest skeletonizing vertebrates and their mineralized feeding apparatus interpreted as having performed a tooth function. However, the absence of jaws in conodonts and the small size of their oropharyngeal musculature limits the force available for fracturing food items, presenting a challenge to this interpretation. We address this issue quantitatively using engineering approaches previously applied to mammalian dentitions. We show that the morphology of conodont food-processing elements was adapted to overcome size limitations through developing dental tools of unparalleled sharpness that maximize applied pressure. Combined with observations of wear, we also show how this morphology was employed, demonstrating how Wurmiella excavata used rotational kinematics similar to other conodonts, suggesting that this occlusal style is typical for the clade. Our work places conodont elements within a broader dental framework, providing a phylogenetically independent system for examining convergence and scaling in dental tools.
title: Jawless vertebrate had world's sharpest teeth

description:
Palm oil is an ingredient in thousands of products we use every day. But palm oil has a dirty secret: forest destruction. Every year, thousands of hectares of Indonesian rainforest and peatlands - some of the most biodiverse regions on the planet - are being destroyed to make way for new palm oil plantations. We don't have to clear forests for palm oil - solutions exist and some companies are on track to supply clean, responsible palm oil. But we need to take urgent action.

We are calling on companies to guarantee their products are free from forest destruction. Clean, responsible palm oil is possible. Join the movement now, and help to Protect Paradise.

protectparadise.org
title: Protect Paradise: An Animation about Palm Oil

description: The Egyptian Vulture (Neophron percnopterus) is a small Old World vulture, found widely distributed from southwestern Europe and northern Africa to southern Asia. It is the only living member of the genus Neophron. It has sometimes also been known as the White Scavenger Vulture or Pharaoh's Chicken. Like other vultures it soars on thermals and the underwing black and white pattern and wedge tail make it distinctive. It sometimes uses stones to break the eggs of birds making it one of the few birds that make use of tools. Birds that breed in the temperate region migrate south in winter while tropical populations are relatively sedentary. Populations of this species have declined in the 20th Century and some isolated island forms are particularly endangered.
title: Rare Egyptian Vulture (Neophron percnopterus) video by shirishkumar Patil

description: I finished this 11' x 24 ' impressionist landscape recently. It was a last minute decision to document the whole process. Filmed on a foscam security camera, isight and flip camera, the video speed and quality changes frequently(Sorry about that). This project was a great experience forming the initial idea all the way through the installation 20' in the air to the bottom of the painting. It presented many challenges along the way including designing a pulley system to move and temporarily suspend the 200lb canvas for painting. If any of my artist friends are interested, Upper Canada Stretchers designs well engineered stretcher supports for jobs like these. Thanks to my brother in law Ted Evans for writing and playing guitar for this video.

description:
Fiona Shaw reads Bertolt Brechts poem I want to go with the one I love... as part of Duke Specials free after show gig in the main foyer at the National Theatre, London after a performance of Mother Courage and Her Children on 03.10.09. 
I want to go with the one I love...
[Original]
Ich will mit dem gehen, den ich liebe.
Ich will nicht ausrechnen, was es kostet.
Ich will nicht nachdenken, ob es gut ist.
Ich will nicht wissen, ob er mich liebt.
Ich will mit ihm gehen, den ich liebe.
[Translation]
I want to go with the one I love.
I do not want to calculate the cost.
I do not want to think about whether it's good.
I do not want to know whether he loves me.
I want to go with whom I love.
Duke Special has been asked to write and perform 11 new songs for the current production of Brechts Mother Courage at the National Theatre starring Fiona Shaw. 
The soundtrack (recorded by Duke and his Band) is due for release on CD on November 20th 2009. For more information on this CD or to pre-order please visit: http://www.dukespecial.com/dukestore/index.php?main_page=product_info&cPath=2&products_id=74
From his website:
 Duke wrote the music for the songs in the play, and sings them onstage along with the band. Its hard to describe the amazing, ambitious spectacle that this production entails, so Ill leave it to the experts; Fiona Shaw, who plays Mother Courage; The National Theatre; Our trusty Board Members themselves.
The play runs until December 8.
To a download a free 11 track Duke Special sampler Everybody Wants a Little Something containing Song of Fraternization please visit: https://fan.musicglue.com/sale/promoproducts.aspx?ProductId=4A3B12DE-90A4-4034-87B5-A23FBFFBAF02
title: Fiona Shaw reads Bertolt Brechts poem I want to go with the one I love ... at the National Theatre, London 03.10.09

description:
ваз 2107 с двигателем 1,7 без компресора, тазы валят. АвтоВАЗ — Автомобильный Волжский Автомобильный Завод.
Такое необычное и избыточное название было выбрано из-за того что в лихие девяностые, когда все коммерсы кинулись со всех ног регистрировать и патентовать товарные знаки и вообще любые названия, ВНЕЗАПНО обнаружилось соответствие букв «ВАЗ» более чем 9000 разнообразных заводов и контор. При коммуняках всем было похуй, а вновь созданные демократические бюро регистрации от этого фалломорфировали и отказывались регистрировать сотни одинаковых названий. Для обхода этой неприятности и придания оригинальности был придуман костыль в виде такого названия, какое сейчас есть.
Свою жизнь завод начал 20 июля 1966 года, когда Партией было принято решение о создании нового крупного автомобильного завода в городе Тольятти (ныне — Аммиакограде). Завод должен был производить современные широко доступные личные транспортные средства. Ибо тогда уже партийные верхи прекрасно понимали: продукция ГАЗ и АЗЛК изрядно устарела и совершенно не отвечала тогдашнему уровню развития мирового автостроения. Для мировой сверхдержавы это нонсенс и вообще большое западло. Ну и, как бонус, дать больше машин в личное пользование любимым гражданам, так как очередь на «москвичи» была до морковкина заговенья, а получить Волгу без блата было нереально.
title: ваз 2107 с двигателем 1,7 без компресора, тазы валят

description:
Michael Behrens es el autor y compositor de esta bella melodía llamada "TIEMPO DE CAMBIO! con arte de GERHARD RICHTER .
Michael nació el 28 Marzo 1973. Vive en Nedersachsem (Alemania). Estudió en la escuela Primaría St- Jürgen-Frankenburg. Futuro esposo  de Relana, tiene dos hijos Manel y Laura. 
Imágines públicas tomadas de Internet, para componer el vídeo con la música.

A través de Internet, nos hemos puesto en comunicación  para crear los vídeos con sus bellas composiciones de música. Le he creado cuatro vídeos con su música. Espero que Michael, quede satisfecho del resultado. 

He disfrutado muchisimo componiendo los  vídeos y escuchando repetidamente sus  melodías. (Gracias Michael por componer tan bellas músicas)

GERHARD RICHTER: http://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gerhard_Richter

Richter nació en la "Florencia del Elba", la ciudad Dresde, Sajonia, y creció en Reichenau, Baja Silesia, y en Waltersdorf en el interior de la Alta Lusacia.
 
A los 13 años En 1945 sobrevivió en bombardeo de su ciudad natal (ver Bombardeo de Dresden) y su tia Marianne Schönfelder (1917-1945) fue eliminada como parte del programa de [eutanasia] establecido por los Nazis.1 Abandonó la escuela después del décimo grado y emprendió su aprendizaje como pintor de publicidad y de escenarios, antes de estudiar en la Academia de Arte de Dresde. En 1948 terminó su escuela profesional superior en Zittau, y, entre 1949 y 1951, fue educado allí en escritura así como en pinturas de escenario y publicidad. En 1950 su solicitud para entrar en la Hochschule für Bildende Künste Dresden (Universidad de Artes Visuales de Dresde, fundada en 1764) fue rechazada. Finalmente comenzó su estudio en la Academia de Arte de Dresde en 1951. Sus profesores fueron Karl von Appen, Ulrich Lohmar y Will Grohmann.
title: Música instrumental de MICHAEL BEHRENS "Tiempo de Cambio"

description:
Winnie found paralysed on June 20th ... now she can walk and run. But her journey is just at the beginning.

Her story ...
***
RO ? EN below
===
Povestea lui Winnie dateaza deja de 3 luni ...
Pe Winnie am gasit-o pe strada neputandu-se misca pe cand avea o luna si jumatate. Radiografia ne-a aratat ca avea 3 fracturi. Primele 10 zile au fost critice si de tratament intensiv, dar Winnie a trecut cu bine peste acea perioada. Din cauza unor medici incompetenti si indiferenti care nu au vrut sa le asculte cand le spuneam ca este ceva in neregula cu Winnie, ca are o umflatura la burtica si ca piciorul drept s-a umflat foarte mult, Winnie era sa moara. Dar Winnie a avut noroc si am gasit o doamna doctor sufletista, care m-a ascultat cu atentie si surpriza: avea o tumora, o infectie probabil de dinainte de a o gasi eu si care acum se manifesta, infectie care ii cuprinsese deja piciorusul fracturat. Doamna doctor a salvat-o si la dansa mergem de atunci. Winnie nu ar fi supravietuit.
Pe 25 iulie a inceput infiltratiile in coloana si gimnastica de recuperare, dupa ce rana s-a vindecat complet.
A reusit sa faca 10 sedinte, cand o noua incercare a urmat pentru Winnie: brusc s-a constipat si desi pe 15 sept i s-a facut clisma, aceasta nu a avut succes, astfel ca pe 16 septembrie a fost operata. Diagnostic megacolon. Incepand cu acea data, mancarea lui Winnie devenea clasica: doar bobite cu fibre. Si in zilele care au urmat, desi a mancat doar mancarea speciala, constipatia s-a instalat din nou si pe data de 24 septembrie, a suferit o a doua operatie, tot megacolon.

Acum se reface, mananca doar bobite cu fibre inmuiate in apa sau supa. Este vioaie, alearga, are scaune moi si in fiecare zi, a inceput sa faca pisu singurica tot mai mult, si rareori mai este nevoie sa ii golim vezica ... Dar inca are nevoie de acele infiltratii in coloana si gimnastica de recuperare, care au dat rezultate incepand cu cea de-a sasea sedinta. Isi flexeaza piciorusul drept care statea ca un bat, si incepe sa mearga aproape normal. [mai multe detalii aici: https://www.facebook.com/events/248921018649207/?source=1]

***
EN
===
Winnie's story dates back three months already ...
When I found Winnie she was paralysed ... she couldn't move back legs. Had only 5-6 weeks. Radiography showed us he had three fractures. The first 10 days were critical and she had needed intensive care, but Winnie went well over that period. Due to few incompetent and indifferent doctors who would not listen when I told them there is something wrong with Winnie, that she has a bulge in the belly and the back right leg was swollen very much, Winnie was almost to die. But Winnie was lucky and I found a doctor hearted lady which listened me carefully and surprise: Winnie had a tumor, an infection present in her body before find her but who started manifesting at that moment. The doctor saved her and since then that lady become Winnie's personal doctor. Winnie would not have survived.

On July 25th she started the spine infiltrations and gymnastics recovery after the wound has healed completely.
She managed to do 10 sessions, when a new attempt followed for Winnie: suddenly she constipated and although on September 15th was made enema, it wasn't successful. Next day on September 16th was operated again. The diagnostic was: megacolon. Since that time, Winnie's food was just fiber food. And in the days that followed, though only ate special food, the constipation installed again. On September 24th, was needed for the second surgery, with the same diagnostic.

Now is recovering, eating only fiber food soaked in water or soup. It is lively, running around the house, has soft stools each day, started to pee alone and only sometimes she needs help to empty the bladder ... But still needs those spine infiltrations and gymnastics recovery, that have had results starting with the sixth session. She can flex their right foot which before couldn't do it at all and started to walk almost normally. [more details here: https://www.facebook.com/events/248921018649207/?source=1]
title: Winnie   Playing

LA TELA

Este tipo de tela es loneta con motivos navideños, en estas fechas las tiendas de telas se visten de este tipo de lonetas, así que no creo que tengáis problema para encontrarla. El precio aproximado es de 9 euros el metro de media. Pero la podemos encontrar por 7 euros el metro o por 27 euros...

Para realizar este camino de mesa diy, sólo necesitaremos 50 cm. Así que el coste de este diy es de 4,5 euros aproximadamente.

Si queréis realizar este camino de mesa para mesas más grandes que 1 metro, os aconsejo que busquéis telas de loneta de doble ancho.

Excerpted from a Tubefilter article by Sarah Ricard:

I don't know how to say this, so I'll just put it out there in the most straightforward way possible:  There is a show called Retarded Policeman.  And it's funny.

Written and directed by husband-and-wife team Kim Evey and Greg Benson of Mediocre Films (one of the most subscribed to content producers on YouTube), the basic premise of the series is pretty much laid out in the show's theme song: "He is a cop and he's learning-impaired. He's the retarded policeman."

But, believe me, it's so much more.  Well, sort of.

Retarded Policeman, which is, incidentally, also the name of the main character in the show played by Josh "The Ponceman" Perry, is a scripted series about a delightful, adorable, completely corrupt, coked-up and cuddly LAPD officer with Down syndrome.

At this point, you should be either totally intrigued, incredibly disgusted, or both.  Still, some of the funniest jokes ever told are offensive.  And while there are those who maintain that the abhorrent, no matter how hilarious, always has a tinge of hatred, the trend in recent mainstream comedy (most notably with Farrelly Brothers movies, Curb Your Enthusiasm and Family Guy) is to test that theory.

Truth be told, Perry does seem to be having a good time with his character -- there is no question that he's talented and gets into the role.  And it makes for more comfortable viewing when you come to terms with the fact that his character always has the upper hand in any given situation.

The really interesting thing about this series, however, is how we (and YouTube commentors) react to it.

Isn't it wrong to portray the mentally disabled as drugged-up, racist and horny simpletons with a fondness for peeing in refrigerators? Isn't it incredibly insensitive to allow Josh Perry to seemingly betray himself and others with his syndrome by playing a completely id-driven and absurd character, whose sole purpose is to amuse and shock us? Isn't it unfair to give mean people just another reason to snicker at the mentally-challenged? Isn't it uncouth to say 'retarded' in this day and age? In other words, isn't it horrible to laugh at Retarded Policeman?

The humor in Retarded Policeman, and other popular comedies that challenge societal norms and political correctness, has a clever way of turning the focus of the viewer inward.  A powerful device, if you get it.

Of course, there will also be people who will laugh just because of the way the Retarded Policeman says, 'Byeeeeeeee,' when a car drives off.

Either way, though, it works.
title: Gun Fight (with Shay Carl) - Retarded Policeman #29

description:
Watch more How to Quilt videos: http://www.howcast.com/videos/507519-How-to-Thread-Baste-a-Quilt-Quilting

Learn how to baste a quilt from quilting expert Cathy Izzo in this Howcast video.


Now that we've got our completed quilt top and our batting and our backing
taped and layered, we're ready to start basting. How you baste it is going
to depend on how you quilt it. If you are going to machine quilt it, you're
going to want to use safety pins and I can show you. We'll do that. If you
want to hand quilt it, you're probably better off thread basting it. Let's
just give you an idea of how we do it with safety pins.

You're going to always start in the center. You're going to go through all
three layers of fabric trying not to disturb the layering. The idea is you
start at the middle and work your way outward. That way any wrinkles sort
of work themselves out to the edges of the quilt.

You're going to want to put pins approximately, I would say, every four
inches. That's a good rule of thumb. Just keep going. You start on the
outside. Actually, basting is my least favorite part of quilting. Probably
because I usually work on really large bed quilts, and pinning takes kind
of a long time and it's boring and you lean over and your back hurts. It's
a good time to get your really good friends to come over and help you. And
I mean really good friends.

Once you've got your whole quilt top pinned, you can remove your tape and
you're ready to start quilting.
title: How to Baste a Quilt | Quilting

By Genevieve Judge, Local News 8 Reporter

POCATELLO - Thursday night a different kind of lecture was held at Idaho State University in Pocatello.  It was a lecture on unidentified flying objects or UFOs.

Robert Hastings says for the last 30 years the Freedom of Information Act has helped declassify thousands of documents about UFOs.  He says a number of them deal with UFO activity at nuclear weapons sights.

Over the last 35 years, Hastings has interviewed former and retired Air Force personnel and he says they've gone on the record saying that saucer shaped objects have appeared above missiles just before they malfunctioned.

During his hour presentation this evening, Hastings' goal was to let the public know what he's found from declassified information.  Hastings says he has a message for non-believers.

"There is a distinct and fundamental difference between having an opinion and having an informed opinion.  I've done the research for 30 years and they haven't.  If they wish to indulge themselves with their uninformed opinion there is nothing I can do about that," said Hastings.

Hastings has a website set up if you'd like to learn more information about his findings and studies.  You can go to http://ufohastings.com/
title: UFO Lecture Held at Idaho State University in Pocatello

description: Rheumatoid Arthritis or R-A is an inflammatory auto-immune disease affecting the lining of the joints. It is very painful and without treatment can eventually cause deformity and disability. The development and early use of medications called disease-modifying antirheumatic drugs or D-M-A-R-D's not only treat the symptoms but may help slow disease progression.  A new study finds certain patient groups with R-A within Medicare managed health plans, are less likely to receive these medications. Catherine Dolf explains in this week's JAMA Report.
title: 2011-02/01 BENEFICIAL RHEUMATOID ARTHRITIS DRUGS LESS LIKELY FOR CERTAIN GROUPS

description:
A Classe Bivalvia é provavelmente a mais conhecida dentre os moluscos. Quantas vezes você já catou conchinhas na praia? Ou quantas vezes você já tentou cavar a areia para tentar pegar um molusco como esse ao lado? Cada conchinha representa uma parte desse animal, e o nome da classe deriva da constatação que esses animais são formados pela união de duas valvas, ou duas conchas. 


Esses animais são exclusivamente aquáticos, e sua massa visceral, a qual contém todos os órgãos, fica comprimida entre as duas conchas calcáreas, e protegida pelo manto, que se liga a cada concha. O pé musculoso está presente neste grupo, mas na maioria das espécies é retrátil e se projeta na abertura das conchas. Esses animais, diferentemente dos gastrópodes, não possuem rádula e sua cabeça é extremamente reduzida.
title: Bivalvia se alimentando

description:
www.facebook.com/sarahsshout

Unless you're too squeamish, turn the sound up! 

As an EDSer, this is a pretty common occurrence. I'm usually too nervous and shy to talk about it much, but awareness is important, so I'm trying to put myself out there more. Last week when I was about to put my hip back in (as I do with most of my joints many times a day), I thought I'd try to capture it on video since I never get to see myself do this, haha. As far as I know, my hip was subluxed (a partial dislocation), which is quite annoying and painful. Every joint is different (especially from person to person), but when my right hip does this I can almost always get it back by doing what I did in the video. 

So, I decided to upload this as a short informative clip for anyone wanting to see a snapshot of a day in the life of an EDSer, or any friends of mine who are curious about my oddities, or anyone looking to see what a hip going back in sometimes looks/sounds like, or... as a bonus... maybe for anyone who has ever not believed me or any other person dealing with this. =P

Anyways, here you go!

Sarah-Jill =)

More info about EDS:

http://www.ednf.org/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=2202&Itemid=88889278
title: Hip Subluxation Reduction (in Ehlers-Danlos Syndrome)

description: MANCHESTER, Tenn. - Diabetes is a disease tough enough for any family. When a child is one who is diagnosed, it becomes even more difficult to control. One Manchester family found help from an unlikely source: a furry friend named Jubilee.There is nothing like a child and her dog, but this dog could one day help save this little girl's life. For Amy and Adam Green it's been a struggle to make sure Layla has the right amount of insulin. She has Type I Diabetes, which means if her blood sugar is too high it could damage her organs. If it gets too low she could slip into a coma. That is where Jubilee comes in. The dog is trained to smell any fluctuations in the toddler's blood sugar and alert Amy or Adam if something is off. Warren Retrievers in Virginia matched a dog with Layla. They'll continue the training process with the Green family over the next 2 years.Director of Training Cheri Campbell delivered the dog to the Green family, and just moments after meeting Layla, she signaled trouble. Jubilee will paw to signal if Layla's blood sugar is too high or too low. Layla's blood sugar was 260. Normal levels would be between 100-200. After being with the family for just one month, Jubilee may have already saved Layla's life. What looks like an easy game of fetch could save Layla's life one day. Jubie is learning how to fetch and retrieve. She could bring a juice box or even a glucose meter if she needed to.For Layla, it means she has a best friend who will always be watching out for her. An added benefit to having Jubilee: the Greens say taking the dog in public has also helped them educate others on Type I Diabetes.If you would like more information on Warren County Retrievers and their dogs, we have a link posted on Fox17.com under FOX LINKS.
title: Diabetic Alert Dog - Kelly Sutton

description:
Visit http://www.askthehardwareguy.com for more tips. Subscribe for new videos.
For a pet accident like vomit or urine, a mixture of baking soda and vinegar does a great job.

Clean up the vomit and then use a wet rag to remove as much liquid as possible. Pour a thin coating of baking soda over the area to absorb the liquid and odor. You can also work the baking soda into the carpet by hand.

Now mix white vinegar and warm water together in a spray bottle and spray the baking soda. The vinegar and baking soda will interact to help loosen particles and stains. 

Let the area dry and then rinse with warm water. 

Vinegar is a disinfectant, it has antibacterial properties and removes many household odors.

Vinegar works well on most surfaces. I would start with a 50-50 mix with warm water and test a hidden spot if you are worried about colorfastness.

Do not use vinegar on stone, marble or travertine.
title: How to Clean Pet Vomit From Carpet - Remove Pet Stains From Carpet - Vinegar to Clean Carpet

description:
Video abstract of review paper Hunger can be taught: Hunger Recognition regulates eating and improves energy balance published in the open access International Journal of General Medicine by authors Ciampolini M, Lovell-Smith D, Kenealy T et al.

Abstract: A set of spontaneous hunger sensations, Initial Hunger (IH), has been associated with low blood glucose concentration (BG). These sensations may arise pre-meal or can be elicited by delaying a meal. With self-measurement of BG, subjects can be trained to formally identify and remember these sensations (Hunger Recognition). Subjects can then be trained to ensure that IH is present pre-meal for most meals and that their pre-meal BG is therefore low consistently (IH Meal Pattern). IH includes the epigastric Empty Hollow Sensation (the most frequent and recognizable) as well as less specific sensations such as fatigue or light-headedness which is termed inanition. This report reviews the method for identifying IH and the effect of the IH Meal Pattern on energy balance. In adults, the IH Meal Pattern has been shown to significantly decrease energy intake by one-third, decrease preprandial BG, reduce glycosylated hemoglobin, and reduce insulin resistance and weight in those who are insulin resistant or overweight. Young children as well as adults can be trained in Hunger Recognition, giving them an elegant method for achieving energy balance without the stress of restraint-type dieting. The implications of improving insulin sensitivity through improved energy balance are as wide as improving immune activity.
 
Read the review paper here: http://www.dovepress.com/hunger-can-be-taught-hunger-recognition-regulates-eating-and-improves--peer-reviewed-article-IJGM
title: Hunger can be taught - Video abstract 40655
